$ PowerShell: Convert CSV files in a directory to Excel Workbooks

This script is iterates over all `*.csv` files it finds in the specified
directory (`~\work\2021-03-29`) and uses the → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/Microsoft/Office/Interop/Excel[.NET `Microsoft.Office.Interop.Excel` namespace] to convert
the → development/Data/exchange/formats/CSV[CSV files] to → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook[workbooks].

gh|about-Excel|/data-exchange_import-export/CSV/convert-files-in-dir.ps1||

sa:

  The → Windows/PowerShell example that → Microsoft/Office/Excel/data-exchange_import-export/CSV/ps-convert-worksheets-to-CSV[worksheets of workbooks in a directory to CSV files].

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/data-exchange_import-export/CSV
